The post that uses a distract tactic is:
@EmmanuelMacron Europe has to wake up! The biggest nuclear power plant of the Europe is on fire. Right this moment. Russian tanks are firing at nuclear power blocks! @EmmanuelMacron @vonderleyen @eucopresident @EP_Edinburgh @EU_Commission @Europarl_EN @UN @NATO @POTUS @OlafScholz @BorisJohnson

This post shifts the focus from the main topic of Russian aggression against Ukraine to a completely different and unrelated topic - a nuclear power plant being on fire. While this may be a serious issue, it distracts from the main issue of the conflict in Ukraine and the need to address Russian aggression. This tactic can be used to draw attention away from important issues or to create confusion and diversion.

The following post uses a distract tactic by discussing an irrelevant topic:

@EmmanuelMacron Europe has to wake up! The biggest nuclear power plant of the Europe is on fire. Right this moment. Russian tanks are firing at nuclear power blocks!

This post is trying to divert attention from the main topic of closing the sky over Ukraine by bringing up an unrelated and alarming issue of a nuclear power plant being on fire. By introducing this unrelated topic, the post is attempting to sidetrack the audience and shift the focus away from the main message of the campaign.
